# SEO, performance (Lighthouse / Google), and best practices

## Goal

Every change that touches **public routes**, **metadata**, **images**, or **bundles** should keep solid scores in **Google Search Essentials**, **Lighthouse** (Performance, Accessibility, Best Practices, SEO), and **Core Web Vitals** (LCP, INP, CLS).

***

## Technical SEO (non-negotiable for indexable pages)

1. **`NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`** — Must be the real **canonical origin** in production (HTTPS, trailing slash consistent). Used via `getPublicSiteUrl()` in `src/lib/site/publicUrl.ts` for **metadataBase**, absolute OG when needed, **sitemap**, and **JSON-LD**. On Vercel, if missing, there is a **fallback** to `VERCEL_URL`; locally use `http://localhost:3000`.
2. **Metadata** — Routes meant to rank should define **`generateMetadata`** or **`metadata`** with **title** (ideally with root `template`), a useful **description**, and **canonical** / **hreflang** when locales exist (`alternates.canonical`, `alternates.languages`, `x-default` aligned with `defaultLocale` in `src/lib/i18n/dictionaries.ts`).
3. **`robots.ts` / `sitemap.ts`** — Keep them aligned: **do not** list in the sitemap routes that must be **noindex** (e.g. authenticated tools). Private or back-office pages should export **`robots: { index: false, follow: false }`**.
4. **Structured data** — Organization/business: prefer **JSON-LD** aligned with `schema.org`, using **`getBrandPublic()`** (which reads `SYSTEM_PROPERTIES_DEFAULTS` + `site_themes` overrides), not stray brand literals.
5. **Branding in copy** — Titles/descriptions mentioning name or tagline follow **01-design-system** (single brand source).

***

## Performance and Lighthouse

1. **`next/image`** — Images need **explicit dimensions** or `fill` + stable container; **`priority`** only for **LCP**; everything else **lazy** by default.
2. **Fonts** — `next/font`: **`display: swap`**, **`adjustFontFallback: true`** when supported; avoid unnecessary font stacks.
3. **Bundles** — Prefer **narrow** imports (e.g. icons); keep **`experimental.optimizePackageImports`** for packages listed in `next.config.ts` while upgrades still support it.
4. **`next.config`** — Honor **`images.formats`** (AVIF/WebP), reasonable **`minimumCacheTTL`**, already-defined lightweight **security** headers; do not disable **compress** in production.

## Performance & accessibility budgets (critical UI)

Changes touching **LCP** (hero, landing, first view of public dashboard), **dense lists**, **main-flow modals**, or **large bundles** must not **hurt LCP / INP / CLS** without **before/after measurement** (local Lighthouse or Vercel/Web Vitals on preview).

1. **Before merge** — Run Lighthouse (or equivalent) on the affected route on **mobile**; note **LCP**, **INP** (or **TBT** as proxy where INP is unavailable), and **CLS** if the change introduces layout shift.
2. **Regression** — If metrics materially regress, justify with mitigation (lazy load, less client JS, `next/image`, splitting `'use client'`) or revert; avoid blind merges.
3. **Accessibility** — Same Lighthouse **Accessibility** pass on touched screens; fix **new** contrast or naming issues unless documented as accepted (aligned with **`01-design-system.mdc`**).
4. **Local automation** — with the dev server: `BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000 npm run lighthouse:smoke` (script `scripts/lighthouse-smoke.sh`, Performance + Accessibility). For **several previews / tenants**, use **`docs/runbooks/accessibility-multi-tenant.md`** (`npm run lighthouse:a11y:tenants` + manifest). In CI, optional nightly/manual jobs exporting HTML as artifacts.

***

## Checklist when adding a public route

- [ ] **title/description** and **canonical** (and translations if applicable)?
- [ ] Should the URL be in **sitemap**? If not, **noindex**?
- [ ] Solid **LCP** (image or text) without harsh CLS?
- [ ] Consistent **OG/Twitter** (or correctly inherited layout defaults)?
- [ ] No **duplicate branding** outside the brand layer (`SYSTEM_PROPERTIES_DEFAULTS` + `site_themes`) / brand helpers?

***

## Repo references

- Public origin: `src/lib/site/publicUrl.ts`
- Locale layout + hreflang + default OG: `src/app/[locale]/layout.tsx`
- JSON-LD: `src/components/molecules/JsonLdOrganization.tsx`
- Sitemap / robots: `src/app/sitemap.ts`, `src/app/robots.ts`
